the star of a cambodian dance troupe decided to 
remain in the united states wednesday when the rest of the company 
went home her lawyer said 
yim devi was the fifth dancer in the 32member cambodian 
classical dance company to defect during its national tour the 
first uscambodian artistic exchange since 1971 
devis attorney martin garbus refused to describe devis act 
as a defection saying her passport is valid until december 
shes going to explore her options he said she might 
stay two days she might stay a week who knows she may want to 
pursue her studies here 
devi was among several troupe members who reported receiving 
death threats during their tour tour organizers alleged that a 
network of cambodianamericans was pressing the dancers to defect 
