here are major provisions in a democratic 
deficitreduction plan approved by the house tuesday 
indexing forgo for one year the annual adjustments to income 
tax brackets and personal exemptions which are designed to protect 
against inflationcaused bracket creep that would mean higher 
income taxes in 1991 for everybody except the wealthiest 
tax rates raise the 28 percent top rate paid by the wealthiest 
people single people with taxable income over 97620 and couples 
above 162770 to 33 percent impose a 10 percent surtax on those 
with taxable incomes over 1 million 
gasoline unlike other plans the bill contains no change in 
taxes on gasoline or heating oil 
alcohol raise the 1250agallon tax on 100proof liquor by 
1 double the beer tax to 32 cents a sixpack raise taxes on most 
wines including for example table wine which would go from 3 
cents a 750milliliter bottle to 25 cents 
tobacco raise the 16cent cigarette tax by 4 cents in 1991 and 
another 4 cents in 1993 snuff cigars and other tobacco would face 
25 percent tax increases each year 
flying raise the 8 percent tax on airline tickets to 10 
percent 
luxuries impose a 10 percent tax on the portion of the price of 
cars above 30000 private boats and planes above 100000 
jewelry above 5000 and furs above 10000 
capital gains allow a person to avoid tax on half of up to 
200000 of capital gains earned in a lifetime the gains could 
come from most investments but not from stocks a person with 
annual income under 100000 could avoid tax on an additional 
1000 a year of gains including those on the sale of stock no 
capital gain would be taxed at a rate above 28 percent 
lowincome increase the earnedincome tax credit which 
benefits lowincome families with children as a way of offsetting 
some of the increased excise taxes 
medicare taxes increase to 100000 the maximum annual wage to 
which the 145 percent medicare tax applies the tax is withheld as 
part of the social security tax 
medicare premiums raise the 2860 monthly premium for medicare 
part b insurance to 2990 next year and 4620 by 1995 
medicare deductible raise to 100 through 1995 the present 75 
deductible which beneficiaries must pay before medicare starts 
paying for doctor bills 
social security require all state and local government workers 
who are not covered by a public retirement plan to pay social 
security taxes 
