the national survey conducted by louis harris and associates 
found 57 percent of 1865 high school students questioned had 
witnessed or heard about a racial incident students in grades 10 
through 12 in public private and parochial schools responded to 
questionnaires between august 31 and september 18 
acts considered racially motivated included taunts graffiti and 
violent acts against people of a particular religion or race said 
