seemed likely to draw support only from serbia and the tiny 
republic of montenegro 
according to tanjug the plan foresees a bicameral parliament 
with one chamber elected on the principle of one man one vote 
opponents say this would give serbs the largest ethnic group in 
yugoslavia with about 9 million people a dominant say in national 
affairs 
the plan also foresees yugoslavia remaining a federation and 
accords member states the right to decide the fate or existence of 
any provinces 
that would give serbia the right to abolish the province of 
kosovo an ancient serbian region now dominated by ethnic 
albanians 
