weeks after the detroit fundraiser sources have said 
riegles chief aide says the fundraiser was scheduled months 
before the april 9 meeting 
riegle has portrayed himself as having only minor involvement in 
the lincoln affair in his letter to the ethics committee he said 
he attended the meeting at the request of deconcini and mccain 
because of his knowledge of the banking industry 
at no time did i seek any meeting with regulators in lincolns 
behalf or suggest any course of regulatory action with respect to 
lincoln he said in a statement last october 
but riegle later acknowledged discussing the lincoln situation 
with gray in march 1987 gray has said that conversation led to the 
two meetings between senators and federal regulators that are a 
focal point of the controversy 
