federal authorities are struggling to estimate 
the size and reach of an elaborate credit card fraud scheme 
masterminded by a murder convict from his prison cell 
daniel neal faries has admitted he used a telephone and computer 
smuggled into his prison cell in florida to purchase hundreds of 
thousand of dollars worth of merchandise on other peoples credit 
cards 
later he even built his own phone within the federal prison in 
chicago to continue running the massive credit card fraud ring 
while he awaited charges of being a leader in the ring 
in newspaper interviews and statements quoted in court records 
