gifts sent flowers and jewelry to his wife and even bought a se 
of diamondstudded false teeth for a fellow inmates mother 
he is scheduled for sentencing thursday in us district court 
in milwaukee he faces five years on the fraud charge and has asked 
the judge to give him the maximum so he can quickly return to 
prison and start a new scheme 
so far authorities have tracked down 500000 worth of 
merchandise stolen through his credit card scam but investigators 
said faries and a ring of up to 125 people could have illegally 
charged millions of dollars more in merchandise to other peoples 
credit cards 
