leaders of the nations two biggest religious 
bodies the roman catholic and southern baptist churches are 
protesting proposals to cut tax deductions for charitable 
contributions 
scores of other voluntary agencies also are opposing the move 
monsignor robert n lynch general secretary of the national 
conference of catholic bishops said weakening the incentives 
for contributions would not only be counterproductive but 
contradict the repeated calls by president bush for increased 
involvement by the nonprofit private sector in addressing needs of 
the less fortunate in our society 
kay s dowhower director of the governmental affairs office for 
the evangelical lutheran church in america noted individuals 
contributed 96 billion in 1989 to various causes serving public 
purpose 
in fact the charitable contribution tax deduction may indeed 
be one of the biggest bargains in the federal budget she said 
adding do not bite the hand that feeds so many 
 
geneva ap hailing the reunification of germany the rev 
emilio castro general secretary of the world council of churches 
urged german churches west and east to learn from each other 
pray and work together and be witnesses together to jesus christ 
at a period when your country needs you most 
 
mexico city ap a canadian television news anchor says 
journalists should broaden the definition of news beyond disasters 
and conflicts to embrace inspiring news that promotes dignity 
kevin evans an anchor for the cbc in vancouver british 
columia said at a lutheransponsored international conference on 
communication that unpleasant news and conflict should be reported 
not as entertainment but to provoke thought to challenge 
 
anchorage alaska ap for the second time in a year an 
american indian has been elected an episcopal bishop the rev 
steven charleston 41 an oklahomaborn choctaw was elected bishop 
of alaska 
another american indian bishop steven plummer was elected a 
year ago as bishop of navajoland a mission diocese based in 
farmington nm covering navajo reservations in arizona new 
mexico and utah 
 
new york ap american orthodox rabbis have designated 
saturday a sabbath of protest against what they called the 
unjust and immoral united nations condemnation of israel for 
the violence in jerusalem in which 19 palestinians were killed 
this hypocrisy of the un is not unusual but the united 
states joining in the condemnation vote is alarming declared 
rabbi marc d angel president of the rabbinical council of 
america the us has betrayed israel 
the conference of presidents of major american jewish 
organizations said the blatant provocation and premeditated act 
of violence in which palestinians hurled rocks at jewish 
worshippers was instigated by plo leaders to divert attention from 
the persian gulf crisis and divide arab states 
 
horsleys green england ap representatives of various 
agencies involved in bible distribution say the world has a 
greater openness and hunger for the word of god than ever before in 
history 
saying that use and familiarity with scriptures had dimished in 
industrial countries the bible organizations urged churches to 
make the scriptures central to their worship and ministry 
the 12 bible organizations holding their first joint meeting 
oct 25 said in a statement 
christian missions often carry out their evangelistic task 
without using the distribution of scripture as an integral part of 
their outreach thereby neglecting to provide their personnel with 
the tool most crucial to their ministry 
the agencies include the united bible societies wycliffe bible 
translators international bible society bibles for the world 
bible league institute for bible translation and pioneer bible 
translators 
