<TEXT>
when dale randolphs organization decided nine years ago to 
translate the bible into modern russian he had no idea how it 
could be useful to the russian people since their country then 
barred importing bibles 
but that project of uncertain ends has turned out to meet a 
surprising and newly expanding purpose 
when we started i didnt have the slightest idea what we 
could do he said in those days it was illegal even to walk 
around the streets of moscow with a bible 
despite the uncertainty the translation work went ahead simply 
in faith without any known feasible usefulness he said 
but by the time the sevenyear job was finished in 1988 he 
said the doors had swung wide open to an immense pentup 
russian yen for bibles a yearning now being served by randolphs 
group and other american organizations 
like others i didnt have any idea the situation was going to 
change he said in an interview the only explanation is that 
someone other than us was watching over this our ministry has been 
blessed over and over in incredible ways 
randolph president of the world bible translation center in 
fort worth texas said a printing of 100000 of its new testaments 
was scheduled for completion in moscow on saturday and would be 
sold through soviet bookstores 
printing of an additional 300000 copies was contracted with a 
grand rapids mich plant as the first part of a goal of 1 million 
copies to be given free to russians by years end plans call for 
handing out a million complete bibles next year 
they will be distributed partly through a branch bible 
center opened in moscow this fall as part of the kuntsevo 
cultural center 
the demand for bibles is just incredible said randolph who 
has made five trips to the soviet union this year arranging the 
project when freedom came it was like a dam had been broken 
and the desire came gushing forth 
the people have been totally starved for the bible theyve 
been starved for information about god everyone in that country is 
wanting to know what christianity is about from government on 
down 
they want to look at what it says about family life about 
alcoholism and other problems to see its answers to life there is 
a tremendous hunger for it the opportunities over there are just 
benumbing 
other agencies also are swelling the flow of bibles to the 
soviet union including the american bible society in which most 
denominations participate and the evangelical publishers 
association in a special moscow project 
those bibles however are in the 17th century russian 
synodal translation as traditionally used by the russian 
orthodox church and other russianlanguage churches 
were the only group providing a modern russian translation 
randolph said were shooting at the masses its not so 
necessary to reach church people as to reach the man in the 
street 
randolphs organization which also produces modern translations 
in other major languages and a simpleenglish version for the deaf 
said two key principles are followed that the rendering be true 
to the original hebrew and greek and be easily understood in the 
target language 
started in 1972 the center is associated with the churches of 
christ for which randolph formerly was a missionary in greece the 
staff of about a dozen includes three scholars in greek and hebrew 
who oversee adherence of the modernlanguage translations to the 
original meanings 
shortly after the center completed its russian new testament 
randolph got a firsthand sampling of the russian appetite for 
bibles at a moscow book fair in september 1989 
his booths supply of 10000 copies was exhausted in one 
morning and for the next day and a half names and addresses were 
taken of 17000 other muscovites wanting bibles these later were 
sent 
the center since has completed the entire bible in modern 
russian 
randolph said much of the change in the soviet union has its 
roots in religious desires in a hungering of citizens in that 
country and most of eastern europe to know more about god 
everthing points to a surge forward of christianity in that 
country he said 
he said that with the soviet union moving toward capitalism the 
people may seek to find their answers to life in western 
materialism but there also is a powerful religious base despite 70 
years of communist efforts to eradicate it he said 
the russian orthodox church is at a high point of its 
existence he said adding the soviet union very well may 
provide a major thrust to christianity in the years ahead 
</TEXT>
