<TEXT>
the television networks race to announce who 
won on election night is over and the winner is vrs 
vrs 
this year for the first time abc cbs nbc and cnn have put 
together a single organization voter research and surveys or vrs 
for exit polls and projections this means two things the 
networks will save money and the main competitive aspect in tv 
election coverage is gone 
of course its being changed no question said warren 
mitofsky executive director of vrs but now i think the networks 
have an opportunity to compete on a much better playing field 
instead of competing about who can come up with numbers first 
they can compete on their news coverage they have a good chance to 
do their analysis their interpretation of what it means and a 
good presentation 
vrs will cost each member 3 million through the 1992 fall 
elections said mitofsky the networks wont say how much theyre 
saving with vrs but they use the word substantial most often 
in their descriptions 
in this age nobody wants to lose a lot of money on news and 
elections never paid their way said mitofsky who led cbss 
election unit for 20 years the commercial revenue from election 
night maybe paid less than a third of the cost this was a very 
expensive proposition without much return 
for 3 million each network gets exit polls and projections for 
all senate house and governors races and they get the same 
information on a selected few state and local races of national 
interest like the washington mayors race and californias 
propositions 
the numbers will be the same but how we interpret that 
information how we use it will be different said mary klett 
nbcs director of elections and polling 
vrs has about 55 people working on the 1990 elections with a 
permanent staff of about half that mitofsky said vrs absorbed 
many of its people from cbs election unit and layoffs from other 
network election units 
in hindsight the broadcast networks decision to form vrs seems 
almost inevitable given that since 1985 all three have changed 
hands or leadership at cbs under laurence a tisch at the merged 
capital citiesabc inc and at nbc under general electric the 
mandate has been to cut costs 
the new arrangment does nothing to prevent any or all of the 
networks from projecting the winner of a presidential election 
before polls close in the west mitofsky said the only longterm 
solution to that problem is a federal uniform pollclosing law 
mitofsky said the oldstyle competition wasnt more accurate 
than vrs all three tended toward more than 99 percent accuracy 
with less pressure to be first the process should be even more 
accurate mitofsky said 
one of the criticisms of what were doing is that therell be 
no way to correct mistakes said mitofsky who for two decades 
headed cbs election unit this is absolute nonsense 
projections derive from three statistical models the first and 
fastest is the exit poll interviews with voters who have cast 
their ballots 
then comes the key precinct model precincts which historically 
have reflected larger voting trends and finally there is the 
county model where projections are based on actual raw vote 
totals 
when you get all done with the three sources of projections 
you then end up with the tabulation of the vote mitofsky said 
this is a selfcorrecting process i dont need to get a phone 
call from nbc to tell me when ive made a mistake 
creating vrs has not been painless negotiations began after the 
1988 elections and concluded only in february of this year the vrs 
questionnaires were designed by negotiation among the network 
election units 
above and beyond that basic service vrs participants can buy 
unilateral polling and projections cbs with the new york 
times has done exactly that arranging for an independent poll of 
voter attitudes 
there is a precedent for vrs the news election service the 
votecounting pool established by abc cbs nbc united press 
international and the associated press in the late 1960s 
vrs is a collection agency and provides only one projection 
said carolyn smith head of abcs election unit vrs provides no 
analysis it is up to the individual network to make the proper 
conclusions and interpretations of the exit polls 
the stuff each network puts out should be more interesting 
she said because weve been able to spend more time figuring out 
what were going to do with this information instead of being 
constantly pressured to be firstest with the mostest 
i assume that the other networks have their own resources and 
may very well come up with their own conclusions even to the 
extent that we may be using a common pool of exit polling said 
marty plisner executive political director for cbs news and a vrs 
project overseer 
the four different networks each have their own style own 
people own signature and to a considerable degree their own 
following plisner said youll know whether youre watching 
cbs or nbc he said beyond that theres a lot more to an 
election than who won and what time you know it 
the most obvious change for viewers should be the way networks 
announce the projections mitofsky said he has asked the networks 
to credit vrs i told them they should he said id like to 
think that they will 
</TEXT>
