happy halloween viewers our topic is bad 
television television that does not create a burden on the 
viewers wit and intellect but induces a vaccuum this is tv so 
bad its scary 
aaaggggghhhhhhhhh 
please save your screams for the end 
were talking about tv that represents deformities in the 
national character tv that speaks of profound problems in the 
republic 
when future historians close the books on our era they may 
forgive american culture for the aberrant values implicit in the 
beverly hillbillies theyll probably call it classic 
television the french will honor gilligans island as a work 
of genius 
it already is happening 
green acres isnt stupid its surreal gushed cables 
nickelodeon channel in plugging its revival of the show 
thats the strange thing about bad television it is preserved 
in reruns until the dignity of age and nostalgia accrete to it 
mediocre tv sinks without a trace bad tv becomes a cultural 
artifact a precious relic of bygone days 
precious relics of the 70s and 80s 
heres a bottom 10 list in ascending order of horror 
 
10 threes company from midseason in 1977 to 1984 this 
show epitomized the central values of the 1970s much like disco 
and leisure suits it was and is appalling 
the premise if that is what it can be called was that two 
women and one man suzanne somers joyce dewitt and john ritter 
were capable of hilarious sexual tension and innuendo while 
chastely sharing an apartment 
this menage was acceptable to the ropers their virtually 
impotent landlord and his sexstarved wife who labored under the 
misapprehension that the male tenant was homosexual a laff riot 
the writing was as predictable as the tides the conflicts were 
trivial the humor sophomoric and the acting ludicrously bad to 
nonexistent at a loss for comic ideas the writers would have 
somers sunbathe when in doubt jiggle 
the show wrecked somers career after she made salary demands 
inconsistent with the producers estimate of her worth john ritter 
may recover joyce dewitt is a future trivia question 
and it is said there is always an episode of threes 
company playing somewhere 
 
9 tie the love boat and fantasy island mind 
candy was how these hourlong abc anthology series were described 
by their fans 
love boat followed a cruise ship and its crew members with 
secondtier guest stars occupying three story lines about couples 
facing various impediments to the course of true love this show 
made barbi benton a star 
it is impossible to convey the unreality of love boat 
situations and characters because they obeyed conventions of 
thought behavior and dress that existed only on television 
sometimes only on the love boat 
