hi im julie your cruise director was fired because of a 
raging debilitating cocaine addiction that remains obvious to even 
the most casual viewer 
it also produced a us congressman harvardeducated fred 
gopher grandy riowa 
 
7 hollywood squares a panel of celebrities waiting in the 
interstices of a tictactoe grid three in a row and you win 
celebrity quips celebrity innuendos coached panelists 
dreadful still it was one of the few settings where liberace 
seemed to be comfortable relaxed and spontaneous 
 
6 the dukes of hazzard cbs hugely successful kid program 
about two vaguely appalachian vaguely southern good ol boys tom 
wopat and john schneider and their beloved car the general lee 
440 dodge charger 1969 
the plot lines werent tough to diagram conflict crisis car 
chase end of car chase end of conflict 
the slapstick was bad and the duke boys dialogue even worse 
wopat and schneider complained about the poor quality of the 
scripts nobody cared the actors claimed they were getting ripped 
off on merchandising and royalties warner bros denied it 
wopat and schneider struck sued warner bros countersued and 
hired replacement dukes the shows ratings plummeted a settlement 
was reached and wopat and schneider returned to the show 
the stars careers have not flourished warner bros remains in 
the entertainment business to this day 
