communications inc in 1985 the third transaction alleges insider 
trading in securities of caesars world inc in 1983 
on tuesday the government implied but offered no proof that the 
prospect of multimilliondollar fees may have motivated milken and 
drexel to break the law to help wickes retire an expensive 
preferred security 
