deltas annual sales tax liability on jet fuel to 4 million that 
would require an act of the general assembly and wilkinson said he 
expects it to pass 
the governor said the state also will grant tax credits worth as 
much as 15 million on the airlines increase in payroll 
the state is offering no incentive money up front for the 
expansion which is expected to add 2800 employees to the 
airlines workforce in northern kentucky 
the project will add 25 arrival and departure gates to the delta 
hub already in place at the airport in boone county the number of 
gates for international departures will double to six 
delta chairman ronald w allen who appeared with wilkinson at 
an airport news conference said the expansion would be the largest 
the airline has ever undertaken cincinnati is the airlines 
fourthlargest hub behind atlanta dallasfort worth and salt lake 
city and has been deltas fastestgrowing allen said 
the airline is to begin construction immediately and is 
scheduled to complete the project by 1994 
wilkinson said 4 million the amount of the proposed sales tax 
limit is what delta is expected to be paying at current prices in 
sales tax on aviation fuel within a year the state receives 15 
million from all airlines officials said 
it was not immediately possible to determine the full value of 
the credits and exemptions for delta but allen said delta projects 
the amount of jet fuel it purchases at the airport would roughly 
double 
the sales tax limit and other elements of the incentive package 
will be placed on the agenda of a planned special session of the 
legislature in january wilkinson said 
the tax limit would apply to any airline that invests 300 
million in kentucky and purchases at least 100 million gallons of 
fuel each year in the state 
