the maker of bunnies biodegradable disposable 
diapers has agreed to stop claiming that its product is good for 
the environment new york attorney general robert abrams announced 
wednesday 
the company had claimed that bunnies and the plastic bag they 
are sold in will biodegrade before your child grows up 
but abrams asserted that bunnies like any organic waste will 
take decades to degrade in our nations landfills 
abrams as lead attorney for 10 states said bunnies maker 
american enviro products inc of placentia calif also agreed to 
pay 50000 to the states for costs and to change the design of the 
diaper so that it really does have less of an impact on the 
environment 
this is a significant settlement because it is the first 
multistate agreement in the greenmarketing area to actually 
reach a cash settlement and move a company in a positive 
direction abrams said 
bunnies has been on the market about a year and a half and 
nationally represents about 1 or 2 percent of the market said the 
companys president robert chickering 
