<TEXT>
crude oil prices tumbled more than 2 a barrel 
wednesday as the energy futures market though still sensitive to 
developments out of the middle east temporarily ran out of steam 
traders were preoccupied with supplyanddemand concerns 
the november contract for light sweet crude oil slumped 217 to 
3672 a 42gallon barrel on the new york mercantile exchange 
later contract months also fell sharply 
with no substantive developments from the persian gulf to 
influence trading the market was swayed by reports that crude was 
going unsold in spot markets the reports indicated low demand for 
oil from refineries which are currently retooling to turn out more 
heating oil rather than gasoline for the winter months 
wednesdays drop was something of a surprise after the previous 
session when crude prices rose nearly 1 on expectations that the 
american petroleum institutes weekly report on inventories 
issued after the close of trading tuesday would indicate a 
decline in stockpiles 
tha is exactly what the api reported the trade group said 
domestic crude inventories fell to 3433 million barrels in the 
week ended oct 12 from 3495 million a week earlier with most of 
the decline coming from a major reduction in imports 
the api report sent oil prices higher overseas but when the 
us market opened prices fell 
technical factors also figured into wednesdays session as the 
price of crude fell through psychological points known as support 
levels selling began to accelerate analysts said 
analysts said the market has lost some of its frenzy since the 
november contract for crude was unable to break through the 
41abarrel mark last week 
but they were quick to caution that despite declines like 
wednesdays the market retains most of its bullishness and it is 
still hypersensitive to any negative developments in the persian 
gulf 
it could rocket up if war breaks out said jim fiedler an 
analyst with e d amp f man international futures inc who called 
wednesdays drop a correction to a bull market 
prices for refined products also fell sharply wednesday 
home heating oil for november delivery plunged 575 cents to 
9825 cents a gallon despite the approaching winter weather later 
contract months also fell sharply 
wholesale unleaded gasoline for delivery in november skidded 
448 cents to 9340 cents a gallon with subsequent months also 
dropping 
in natural gas trading the november contract closed at 1900 
per 1000 cubic feet down from 1910 on tuesday 
