ames department stores inc the ailing 
discount chain that filed for bankruptcy protection earlier this 
year said wednesday it will lay off 250 corporate employees and 
close offices in west hartford and syracuse ny 
the rocky hillbased company said it already has eliminated 200 
corporate positions through attrition over the past four months 
the company has 1600 corporate employees 
both moves are part of the companys plan to reduce costs as it 
struggles to recover under bankruptcy protection the bulk of the 
layoffs 160 will be from syracuse ny 
ames said the west hartford merchandising operations and 
syracuse ny finance operation will be relocated in rocky hill 
next spring 
ames filed for protection from its creditors april 25 the 
filing under chapter 11 of the us bankruptcy code allows the 
company to remain in business while it works out a plan to repay 
its creditors 
since filing for bankruptcy protection the company has closed 
219 stores and laid off about 18000 employees 
