bond prices finished little changed wednesday 
influenced by mixed economic reports more middle east uncertainty 
unresolved budget talks in washington and plans for a record 2year 
treasury note auction 
the treasurys key 30year issue rose about 1 per 1000 in 
face amount its yield which falls when the price rises eased to 
888 percent from 889 percent late tuesday 
bond strategists said commerce department reports showing 
weakness in the housing industry but rising industrial production 
in september injected some confusion into the market because they 
signaled signs of recession and growth at the same time 
that jerked it around a little bit said micheal casey a 
bond economist at maria ramirez capital consultants inc a new 
york investment concern there were various conflicting stories 
out of the mideast that knocked it around a little bit too 
all financial markets have been fixated on developments in the 
persian gulf since iraq seized kuwait more than two months ago 
provoking a crisis that has nearly doubled the price of oil and 
raised fears of both recession and oilshock inflation in the 
united states which imports half its petroleum 
on tuesday bond prices rose slightly on speculation that 
diplomacy might help resolve the mideast crisis but that thinking 
seemed to disappear wednesday partly on secretary of state james 
a baker iiis remarks that iraqs saddam hussein must fail if 
peace is to succeed 
