georgiapacific corp on wednesday reported a 46 
percent drop in profit in the third quarter as its interest expense 
soared and its building products business weakend 
the wood and paper company reported net income of 95 million 
or 111 per share on sales of 34 billion for the three months 
that ended sept 30 in the same period last year profit was 178 
million or 558 per share on sales of 26 billion 
the buyout of great northern nekoosa corp helped boost sales 
but georgia pacifics interest expense rose from 65 million in the 
third quarter of 1989 to 163 million in the most recent quarter 
building products profits dropped in the quarter on lower 
prices said t marshall hahn jr chairman and chief executive 
officer plywood prices dropped 15 percent from the same period a 
year ago he said 
pulp and paper profits improved despite generally lower prices 
he said 
demand and pricing for tissue and communication papers remains 
strong hahn said 
