<TEXT>
a venezuelan computer company has sued american 
telephone amp telegraph co seeking 90 million in damages claiming 
atampt tried to put the company out of business and monopolize the 
phone and computer industries in venezuela 
the lawsuit was filed in federal court in manhattan by ca 
westel de venezuela a former distributor of atampt products in the 
south american nation 
according to a statement from westel the suit claims atampt 
induced the company into buying obsolete or broken atampt equipment 
at inflated prices then slandered the company by telling its 
customers that it was at fault for problems with the equipment 
the suit also alleges atampt attempted to monopolize the 
telecommunications and computer industries in venezuela through a 
pattern of racketeering activity and in furtherance of a scheme 
to defraud according to the statement 
in addition the suit claims that atampt stole telephone 
technology developed by westel 
we havent seen the suit yet but we have had differences with 
this company in recent times that led to the end of our 
relationswhip with them early this year said atampt spokesman andy 
myers reading from a statement 
</TEXT>
